You’re right — you clearly mentioned not to use synchronized, and I appreciate the reminder.

The use of synchronized in the previous version was for safe lazy initialization of the Cosmos client, but since you’ve asked to avoid it, we can fully switch to a concurrent + atomic solution using ConcurrentHashMap.computeIfAbsent() for both the CosmosClient and the containers.

⸻

✅ Here’s a revised version without synchronized, using lazy caching with computeIfAbsent:

import com.azure.cosmos.*;
import com.azure.identity.DefaultAzureCredentialBuilder;
import com.azure.security.keyvault.secrets.SecretClient;
import com.azure.security.keyvault.secrets.SecretClientBuilder;
import com.azure.security.keyvault.secrets.models.KeyVaultSecret;

import java.util.Map;
import java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap;

public class CosmosClientProvider {

    private static final boolean keyVaultEnabled = Boolean.parseBoolean(System.getenv().getOrDefault("AZURE_KEYVAULT_ENABLED", "false"));
    private static final String cosmosUri = System.getenv("COSMOS_URI");
    private static final String cosmosKey = System.getenv("COSMOS_KEY");

    private static final String cosmosDbUriSecretName = System.getenv("COSMOS_URI_SECRET_NAME");
    private static final String cosmosDbKeySecretName = System.getenv("COSMOS_KEY_SECRET_NAME");
    private static final String keyVaultUri = System.getenv("KEYVAULT_URI");

    // Thread-safe caches
    private static final Map<String, CosmosClient> clientCache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
    private static final Map<String, CosmosDatabase> dbCache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
    private static final Map<String, CosmosContainer> containerCache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    private static final String DEFAULT_CLIENT_KEY = "default";

    private CosmosClientProvider() {}

    public static CosmosClient getCosmosClient() {
        return clientCache.computeIfAbsent(DEFAULT_CLIENT_KEY, key -> {
            String uri, keyValue;
            if (keyVaultEnabled) {
                SecretClient secretClient = new SecretClientBuilder()
                        .vaultUrl(keyVaultUri)
                        .credential(new DefaultAzureCredentialBuilder().build())
                        .buildClient();

                uri = secretClient.getSecret(cosmosDbUriSecretName).getValue();
                keyValue = secretClient.getSecret(cosmosDbKeySecretName).getValue();
            } else {
                uri = cosmosUri;
                keyValue = cosmosKey;
            }

            return new CosmosClientBuilder()
                    .endpoint(uri)
                    .key(keyValue)
                    .consistencyLevel(ConsistencyLevel.EVENTUAL)
                    .gatewayMode()
                    .buildClient();
        });
    }

    public static CosmosContainer getContainer(String databaseName, String containerName) {
        String containerKey = databaseName + ":" + containerName;

        return containerCache.computeIfAbsent(containerKey, key -> {
            CosmosDatabase database = dbCache.computeIfAbsent(databaseName,
                    dbName -> getCosmosClient().getDatabase(dbName));
            return database.getContainer(containerName);
        });
    }
}


⸻

✅ Key Benefits
	•	🚫 No synchronized
	•	✅ Uses ConcurrentHashMap.computeIfAbsent() for safe concurrent access
	•	✅ Lazy-loading: nothing is created until needed
	•	✅ Caches CosmosClient, CosmosDatabase, and CosmosContainer efficiently

